FBIS4-8087 "dreeu069_i_94039" FBIS-EEU-94-069 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Direct `Most Intense' Attacks at Doboj Serbs Direct `Most Intense' Attacks at Doboj AU1104111694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 11 Apr 94 AU1104111694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Mirudin Aldobasic report from 7 South Operative Group of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army] [Text] The enemy displayed the most intense activities from (?Sevarlije) and Potocani, with mortars, Bofors guns, antiaircraft machine guns, and antiaircraft guns at the defense lines on the Doboj battlefield and in the zone of responsibility of the Sije independent battalion, as well as at the civilian settlements Mravici, Martuzici, and Ularice. The Chetniks engaged in attacks with antiaircraft machine guns and antiaircraft guns in the zone of responsibility of the 110th Croatian Defense Council Brigade Usora and the Tesanjka independent battalion. The enemy also opened [word indistinct] artillery fire [words indistinct] civilian settlements Mirjanovac and Kalosevci and at the defense positions of the 207th Famous Hill Brigade [word indistinct]. There was no peace in other battlefields on this free territory of our country either. The enemy displayed constant provocations along the defense lines in the zone of responsibility of the 7 South Operative Group, which is 135 km long.
